# =====================================================================
# Data — track curated model INPUTS, ignore large / regeneratable / legacy
# =====================================================================
# Tracked (NOT ignored): data/dna, data/current_rosters, data/external
#   — JSON/CSV inputs the Python engine actually consumes.
# Ignored below: regeneratable caches, runtime state, and legacy R data.
# NOTE: .gitignore does NOT support trailing/inline comments — every pattern
# must be alone on its line, or the comment becomes part of the pattern.

# 295MB training-master CSV + pools (regenerated from nflverse pulls)
data/processed/
# sim-result parquet caches + per-week JSON (regenerated by sim runners)
data/interim/
# runtime bot state (bot_state.db) + live game CSV output
data/live/
data/cache/
# legacy R training splits (.rds) — superseded by joblib model artifacts
data/win_probability/
data/field_goal/
data/fourth_down/

# Model training caches (regenerated on next train run)
*_train_cache.parquet

# =====================================================================
# Legacy archive — keep CODE for reference, ignore superseded DATA/binaries
# =====================================================================
# legacy/ retains the old R/Python implementation as a readable reference
# archive (~6k lines of code). Its data + model binaries (2.35GB, incl. 9
# files over GitHub's 100MB hard limit) are superseded and regeneratable —
# excluded, same principle as the active data/processed/.
legacy/data/
legacy/models_archive/
legacy/**/*.npy
legacy/**/*.pt

Notebooks
R/logs

# R basics
.Rproj.user/
.Rhistory
.RData
.Ruserdata
.Rapp.history
.Renviron


# renv
renv/
renv.lock.bak


# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
# active project virtualenv (Python 3.12) — reproduce via requirements.txt
venv/
.venv/
# temporary fallback from the 3.8->3.12 upgrade; delete once 3.12 is trusted
venv_py38_old/
.pytest_cache/


# Local secrets & runtime
.env
logs/
R/bots/.posted_keys.rds
# Live bot per-game runtime output (regenerated each run; keep only the README)
R/bots/live_csv/*.csv
R/bots/live_csv/*.log


# Data cache & artifacts
*.duckdb
*.sqlite


# OneDrive multi-machine sync-conflict duplicates — stale copies of real files
# (e.g. game_engine-Cams-Desktop.py). Never commit; delete from disk when found.
*-Cams-Desktop.*

# OS/editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.obsidian/
scratch/
